[{"id":"VR852787","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following expressions correctly represents the tension in the cable?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR852787_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A horizontal beam of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> and length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>L</mi> </math></span></span> is attached at one end to a wall and at the other end by a cable extending to the wall. The angle formed by the cable and the horizontal is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span>. A sign of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase M\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"uppercase M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> hangs from the end of the beam furthest from the wall, as shown in the figure.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal beam suspended from a vertical wall to the left, held up by a cable that attaches from the top of the wall to the end of the beam. The angle between the cable and the horizontal is theta. The beam has a length of L and a mass of lowercase m. A sign with mass uppercase M is hanging from the right end of the beam.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR852787.g01.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator open parenthesis, one half lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g, and denominator the sine of theta\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator open parenthesis, one half lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g, and denominator the sine of theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, one half lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, one half lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator open parenthesis, lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g, and denominator the sine of theta\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator open parenthesis, lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g, and denominator the sine of theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, lowercase m plus uppercase M, close parenthesis, times g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]